<Page x:Class="AsynAwaitExamples.Steps.Step23_AsyncTestingPatterns"
      xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
      xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
      xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:AsynAwaitExamples.ViewModels"
      Title="Step 23 - Async Testing">
    <Page.DataContext>
        <vm:Step23ViewModel/>
    </Page.DataContext>
    <ScrollViewer VerticalScrollBarVisibility="Auto">
        <StackPanel Margin="10">
            <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource HeaderStyle}" 
                       Text="Step 23: Async Unit Testing Patterns"/>

            <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource ExplanationStyle}" xml:space="preserve">ASYNC TESTING: How to properly test async code in unit tests.

All major test frameworks (xUnit, NUnit, MSTest) support async Task tests.
Just make your test method "async Task" and use "await" inside.

KEY PATTERNS:
- Basic: [Fact] public async Task MyTest() { var x = await service.GetAsync(); }
- Exceptions: await Assert.ThrowsAsync&lt;T&gt;(() =&gt; service.FailAsync());
  (NOT Assert.Throws! That misses exceptions inside the Task!)
- Cancellation: create a pre-cancelled token, verify OperationCanceledException.
- Timeouts: task.WaitAsync(timeout) prevents tests from hanging forever.
- Mocking: Task.FromResult, Task.CompletedTask, Task.FromException.

This step simulates test runs in the UI. The patterns are directly
transferable to real xUnit/NUnit/MSTest projects.</TextBlock>

            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="? Basic async test pattern"
                    Command="{Binding BasicAsyncTestCommand}"/>
            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="?? Testing async exceptions"
                    Command="{Binding ExceptionTestCommand}"/>
            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="?? Testing cancellation"
                    Command="{Binding CancellationTestCommand}"/>
            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="?? Testing with timeouts"
                    Command="{Binding TimeoutTestCommand}"/>
            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="?? Mocking async dependencies"
                    Command="{Binding MockingTestCommand}"/>

            <TextBox Style="{StaticResource OutputStyle}" Height="260"
                     Text="{Binding OutputText, Mode=OneWay}"/>
        </StackPanel>
    </ScrollViewer>
</Page>
